Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).

Zest and cut the @lime{1}(zested and cut into wedges) into wedges. Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Trim the @green beans{80%g}(trimmed and chopped into thirds).

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{210%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Add the pepper and green beans to the chicken pan. Stir-fry until they start to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the veg has softened, stir in the garlic, lime zest, @bulgogi sauce{100%g} and @soy sauce{25%g}.

Stir-fry until everything's piping hot and the chicken is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the noodles are cooked, add them to the chicken stir-fry and toss to coat in the sauce. Cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of @?water{a splash} if you feel it needs it.

Share the bulgogi chicken noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the peanuts and spring onion for those who'd like them.

Serve with a lime wedge on the side for squeezing over. Enjoy!